WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.289 --> 00:00:03.300
<i>From the moment Sibeth arrived
in Pennsa.</i>

2
00:00:03.385 --> 00:00:05.296
<i>I knew she was gonna be a problem.</i>

3
00:00:05.380 --> 00:00:07.590
<i>I just didn't realize
quite how much of a problem.</i>

4
00:00:07.674 --> 00:00:10.921
I assume you have the former queen
tucked away somewhere.

5
00:00:11.078 --> 00:00:12.819
There's been a bit of a wrinkle.

6
00:00:12.903 --> 00:00:14.154
You don't trust me.

7
00:00:14.428 --> 00:00:17.556
Course not. That's what I like about you.

8
00:00:17.641 --> 00:00:20.242
My bombs will allow us
to conquer their kingdom

9
00:00:20.354 --> 00:00:21.828
and claim it as our own.

10
00:00:21.913 --> 00:00:24.718
Whoever controls the weapons
owns the day.

11
00:00:24.820 --> 00:00:27.277
If the Trivantians have weapons
that can do this.

12
00:00:27.361 --> 00:00:28.977
no one will be able to stop them.

13
00:00:29.062 --> 00:00:30.196
<i>We know where the bombs are.</i>

14
00:00:30.280 --> 00:00:31.614
<i>We are on our way to destroy them now.</i>

15
00:00:36.286 --> 00:00:39.372
Your words border on treason.

16
00:00:39.456 --> 00:00:42.167
Well. then. let's have no more words.

17
00:00:42.251 --> 00:00:44.794
Will you just tell me what's going on...

18
00:00:44.878 --> 00:00:47.338
<i>It was Tormada's weapon.
He destroyed the Triangle.</i>

19
00:00:47.422 --> 00:00:50.259
- This is a coup.
- She was a part of it. And so are you.

20
00:00:51.343 --> 00:00:52.344
The queen is here.

21
00:00:53.470 --> 00:00:56.647
Queen Maghra. This is a surprise.

22
00:00:56.858 --> 00:00:58.968
Maghra is not your queen.

23
00:01:03.976 --> 00:01:06.312
The Witchfinders
served you loyally

24
00:01:06.403 --> 00:01:09.601
and without question
for all the years of your reign.

25
00:01:10.031 --> 00:01:14.632
traveling to the farthest reaches
of the kingdom to rid the world of evil.

26
00:01:15.912 --> 00:01:18.261
Then you rejected the divine doctrines.

27
00:01:19.374 --> 00:01:22.974
tearing us apart
and forcing us into hiding.

28
00:01:24.713 --> 00:01:27.799
Now you say you want us
to serve you once more.

29
00:01:27.883 --> 00:01:30.101
as if all of that never happened?

30
00:01:31.762 --> 00:01:33.151
Yes. that's right.

31
00:01:34.863 --> 00:01:36.669
So I ask you now.

32
00:01:37.305 --> 00:01:39.988
why the fuck would we do that?

33
00:01:40.604 --> 00:01:45.460
Why not just execute you as a heretic
and be done with it?

34
00:01:51.239 --> 00:01:52.879
Lucien is right.

35
00:01:53.992 --> 00:01:57.829
I have caused you all pain and distress.

36
00:01:57.913 --> 00:02:01.805
And for that.
you have my deepest apologies.

37
00:02:04.758 --> 00:02:10.902
My sister. long believed to be dead.
was returned to me.

38
00:02:12.928 --> 00:02:14.568
And in my joy.

39
00:02:15.806 --> 00:02:21.366
and in my gratitude to the God Flame.
I opened my heart.

40
00:02:23.605 --> 00:02:25.495
And my sister bewitched me.

41
00:02:26.149 --> 00:02:29.875
She and her two witch children.

42
00:02:32.656 --> 00:02:34.296
And I lost my way.

43
00:02:36.956 --> 00:02:41.432
Just like you.
I have suffered dearly for it.

44
00:02:42.207 --> 00:02:44.584
I've been in leg irons
for the last nine months.

45
00:02:44.668 --> 00:02:47.039
They starved me. They tortured me.

46
00:02:47.180 --> 00:02:49.499
They took my baby from me.

47
00:02:55.220 --> 00:02:56.485
But it wasn't them.

48
00:02:57.764 --> 00:03:01.865
No. they were merely instruments
of the God Flame herself.

49
00:03:02.728 --> 00:03:03.950
Testing me.

50
00:03:04.813 --> 00:03:08.705
Putting me through trials
to purify my heart once more.

51
00:03:09.192 --> 00:03:13.906
so that I might reclaim my holy kingdom
for the righteous.

52
00:03:14.990 --> 00:03:16.968
And why should we believe you now?

53
00:03:18.171 --> 00:03:19.804
Why should you believe me?

54
00:03:23.123 --> 00:03:25.289
Because I am your queen!

55
00:03:30.881 --> 00:03:32.749
I am your queen.

56
00:03:34.092 --> 00:03:35.982
ordained by God.

57
00:03:36.652 --> 00:03:41.114
And no human will change that.
Not my sister. not the Trivantians.

58
00:03:41.253 --> 00:03:42.585
And not you. Lucien.

59
00:03:45.585 --> 00:03:49.297
It was I who declared war
on the Trivantians.

60
00:03:49.483 --> 00:03:54.042
I who foretold our miraculous victory
at Green hill Gap.

61
00:03:56.077 --> 00:04:01.726
And since then. my execution
has been called for by Tamacti Jun.

62
00:04:02.389 --> 00:04:06.415
by my sister and her corrupted council.
by the Trivantians.

63
00:04:07.143 --> 00:04:11.605
And yet. somehow. none of them
could manage the simple task

64
00:04:11.783 --> 00:04:13.715
of putting a blade to my throat.

65
00:04:14.132 --> 00:04:17.374
nor could their chains hold me.

66
00:04:17.648 --> 00:04:20.320
And the God Flame sent me out
to find you.

67
00:04:21.621 --> 00:04:24.012
You are soldiers with no country…

68
00:04:25.615 --> 00:04:28.476
With no rightful claim to the crown.

69
00:04:29.319 --> 00:04:31.210
One of two fates await you.

70
00:04:31.650 --> 00:04:34.851
You'll either be hunted down
by my sister's army.

71
00:04:35.237 --> 00:04:38.420
or become slaves to the Trivantians.

72
00:04:39.167 --> 00:04:41.141
Why should you believe me?

73
00:04:41.868 --> 00:04:47.226
Because I'm all you've got!
And I love you all!

74
00:04:50.530 --> 00:04:53.882
I am going to take back
the throne of my father.

75
00:04:55.949 --> 00:04:58.937
The God Flame has shown me the way.

76
00:05:01.620 --> 00:05:03.579
And I ask you now.

77
00:05:03.882 --> 00:05:05.439
No. I command you.

78
00:05:06.981 --> 00:05:11.117
in her name. to fight by my side!

79
00:05:11.982 --> 00:05:15.085
To reclaim our holy kingdom!

80
00:05:15.652 --> 00:05:19.336
For God and for yourselves.

81
00:05:20.782 --> 00:05:23.054
My holy warriors!

82
00:05:23.319 --> 00:05:29.609
The true defenders of Paya!

83
00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:37.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

84
00:07:11.018 --> 00:07:12.018
Haniwa.

85
00:07:12.102 --> 00:07:15.438
Did you see him?

86
00:07:15.522 --> 00:07:16.898
- Who?
- Harlan.

87
00:07:16.982 --> 00:07:18.816
- He's out there with the rest of them.
- As a prisoner?

88
00:07:18.900 --> 00:07:20.818
- I don't know. it didn't seem that way.
- Forget Harlan.

89
00:07:20.902 --> 00:07:23.404
When this is over. I will deal with him.
Help me lock this door.

90
00:07:23.488 --> 00:07:25.339
Okay.

91
00:07:51.642 --> 00:07:53.142
All dead. sir.

92
00:07:53.226 --> 00:07:54.407
All of them?

93
00:07:55.604 --> 00:07:57.814
Who was it? Payan soldiers?

94
00:07:57.898 --> 00:08:00.299
If so. none were killed here.

95
00:08:00.734 --> 00:08:02.569
These are all our soldiers.

96
00:08:02.653 --> 00:08:04.501
That doesn't seem likely.

97
00:08:05.197 --> 00:08:08.046
Check the bombs and the children.

98
00:08:10.160 --> 00:08:11.383
Sir.

99
00:08:12.996 --> 00:08:14.177
Set!

100
00:08:19.711 --> 00:08:20.892
Check the house.

101
00:08:22.005 --> 00:08:23.478
Sir!

102
00:08:34.667 --> 00:08:36.335
The door is barricaded.

103
00:08:36.482 --> 00:08:38.873
Barricaded?

104
00:08:39.648 --> 00:08:40.996
So we're not alone.

105
00:08:53.245 --> 00:08:54.885
Keep moving. keep moving.

106
00:08:55.622 --> 00:08:58.333
Wren. I don't need you here.
Go find Haniwa.

107
00:08:58.417 --> 00:09:00.335
I promised their brother
I'd keep them safe.

108
00:09:00.419 --> 00:09:02.017
We don't have time to argue.

109
00:09:02.379 --> 00:09:03.643
I'm staying.

110
00:09:04.298 --> 00:09:07.105
Fine. You're last. Watch our backs.

111
00:09:53.305 --> 00:09:54.820
<i>Four more dead in the lab.</i>

112
00:09:55.223 --> 00:09:56.975
- And the bombs?
- Secure.

113
00:09:57.059 --> 00:09:58.240
Huh.

114
00:09:58.560 --> 00:10:00.103
So it's the children in the building?

115
00:10:00.187 --> 00:10:03.495
The children didn't kill
two dozen soldiers. It's something else.

116
00:10:04.024 --> 00:10:06.373
Maybe they have the children with them or…

117
00:10:07.486 --> 00:10:10.127
Captain Armagon.

118
00:10:11.698 --> 00:10:14.172
Tear these grounds apart.

119
00:10:14.576 --> 00:10:15.841
Find those children.

120
00:10:18.413 --> 00:10:21.207
- And Captain. we need them alive.
- Yes. sir.

121
00:10:21.291 --> 00:10:25.503
Tormada. we came here for the bombs.
Let's take them and go.

122
00:10:25.587 --> 00:10:27.727
As always. thinking too small.

123
00:10:28.256 --> 00:10:31.022
Always in the moment. never ahead.

124
00:10:32.052 --> 00:10:33.900
We've already lost Oloman.

125
00:10:34.388 --> 00:10:37.320
Without the other sighted children.
we'll soon be out of bombs.

126
00:10:37.891 --> 00:10:42.534
I didn't spend all that time developing
these explosives to lose my bomb builders.

127
00:10:47.401 --> 00:10:50.459
- Charlotte.
- I hear them. How close?

128
00:10:53.073 --> 00:10:54.337
Too close.

129
00:11:01.373 --> 00:11:04.055
Over by the tree. Now. Go.

130
00:11:04.793 --> 00:11:07.726
Come on. Get low. Get down.

131
00:11:08.213 --> 00:11:09.394
Close your eyes.

132
00:11:17.931 --> 00:11:19.362
You there.

133
00:11:19.766 --> 00:11:21.448
We don't want to hurt the children.

134
00:11:22.769 --> 00:11:23.950
Then walk away.

135
00:11:24.980 --> 00:11:26.369
Kill her!

136
00:12:33.131 --> 00:12:36.050
Everyone okay? All heads accounted for?

137
00:12:36.134 --> 00:12:38.136
Yes.

138
00:12:38.220 --> 00:12:39.401
Lu?

139
00:12:39.805 --> 00:12:41.611
I'm good.

140
00:12:41.974 --> 00:12:44.239
Okay. We keep moving.

141
00:12:44.726 --> 00:12:46.644
Okay. come on. Always behind me.

142
00:13:12.379 --> 00:13:14.311
I don't know who you are.

143
00:13:15.090 --> 00:13:16.855
And frankly. I don't care.

144
00:13:18.010 --> 00:13:21.276
But if you have my children in there.
then a deal can be made.

145
00:13:22.264 --> 00:13:23.765
They're not your children.

146
00:13:23.849 --> 00:13:26.615
Sheva.

147
00:13:27.477 --> 00:13:30.660
Look at you all grown up
and leading an insurrection.

148
00:13:31.273 --> 00:13:33.330
- I'm impressed.
- Oh. fuck you!

149
00:13:34.568 --> 00:13:36.625
I don't wanna kill you. Sheva.

150
00:13:37.529 --> 00:13:39.419
But I will if I have to.

151
00:13:40.324 --> 00:13:41.797
You and your family.

152
00:13:42.868 --> 00:13:47.010
Now. whoever's in there with you
may not know me. but you do.

153
00:13:47.664 --> 00:13:50.096
So you know I'm coming through
these doors.

154
00:13:57.174 --> 00:13:59.689
I know you better than you think. Tormada.

155
00:14:00.927 --> 00:14:02.317
I know that voice.

156
00:14:06.224 --> 00:14:10.158
Ranger. My old friend.

157
00:14:12.230 --> 00:14:14.607
How I've missed our sessions together.

158
00:14:14.691 --> 00:14:16.248
Yeah. I know!

159
00:14:17.194 --> 00:14:21.128
That's why I gave you all those scars
to remember me by before I left.

160
00:14:21.531 --> 00:14:22.838
Yes.

161
00:14:24.660 --> 00:14:28.121
And I shall remember to keep you alive
long enough to regret that.

162
00:14:28.205 --> 00:14:30.345
Big talk for such a little shit weasel!

163
00:14:53.188 --> 00:14:56.955
His time will come. I promise you.

164
00:14:58.944 --> 00:15:02.919
Ranger. Are you still there?

165
00:15:05.742 --> 00:15:06.923
No?

166
00:15:09.037 --> 00:15:10.927
Who then am I negotiating with?

167
00:15:15.377 --> 00:15:17.309
This is Baba Voss.

168
00:15:19.381 --> 00:15:20.937
And I'm not negotiating.

169
00:15:21.341 --> 00:15:22.564
Baba Voss.

170
00:15:25.137 --> 00:15:28.181
Quite the band of outlaws
you've assembled. Sheva.

171
00:15:28.265 --> 00:15:32.782
Oh. you've done me a great service.
Now I can kill them all at once.

172
00:15:33.103 --> 00:15:35.535
Get these doors open now!

173
00:15:37.232 --> 00:15:38.525
Baba Voss.

174
00:15:38.609 --> 00:15:40.193
A momentary aggravation.

175
00:15:40.277 --> 00:15:42.737
Brought on by your poor impulse control.

176
00:15:42.821 --> 00:15:45.114
I'll admit I misjudged him.

177
00:15:45.198 --> 00:15:47.158
Oh. you admit it. What a relief.

178
00:15:47.242 --> 00:15:48.836
- Can I make a suggestion?
- Harlan...

179
00:15:48.921 --> 00:15:50.161
You promised me he wouldn't speak.

180
00:15:50.245 --> 00:15:54.930
Sheva and her family sold Baba Voss's
daughter to the Trivantians. okay?

181
00:15:55.792 --> 00:15:58.336
He has no love for them.

182
00:15:58.420 --> 00:16:00.880
And judging by the arrows
in your soldiers.

183
00:16:00.964 --> 00:16:03.104
I'd say his daughter is here with him.

184
00:16:03.592 --> 00:16:07.275
And if his daughter's here.
you can bet your balls his son is too.

185
00:16:08.680 --> 00:16:10.807
Give him time to understand he's trapped.

186
00:16:10.891 --> 00:16:14.282
He'll give you the girl
to save his children. I guarantee it.

187
00:16:14.686 --> 00:16:16.117
Lord Harlan.

188
00:16:17.189 --> 00:16:18.912
You might be of some use after all.

189
00:16:20.359 --> 00:16:21.706
Baba Voss!

190
00:16:23.737 --> 00:16:26.239
I understand you have
your children with you.

191
00:16:26.323 --> 00:16:31.383
the legendary Haniwa and Kofun
of the battle of Green hill Gap.

192
00:16:32.579 --> 00:16:34.622
I don't have children. so I'm no expert.

193
00:16:34.706 --> 00:16:39.057
but it seems to me you've got a habit
of putting them in harm's way.

194
00:16:40.629 --> 00:16:42.589
Would you really let your children die

195
00:16:42.673 --> 00:16:45.689
protecting the family
that sold your daughter to Edo?

196
00:16:47.386 --> 00:16:49.901
Return Sheva and her siblings to me.

197
00:16:50.764 --> 00:16:52.237
and I give you my word.

198
00:16:53.892 --> 00:16:56.283
Haniwa and Kofun will live.

199
00:16:59.481 --> 00:17:01.455
But if I have to come in and get them.

200
00:17:02.067 --> 00:17:04.666
then everybody dies.

201
00:17:07.155 --> 00:17:09.004
I'll give you some time to think about it.

202
00:17:23.505 --> 00:17:24.811
I should give myself up.

203
00:17:25.841 --> 00:17:28.982
It was my family that wronged you.
Let me go and make this right.

204
00:17:33.890 --> 00:17:35.864
You were forced to work for that man.

205
00:17:36.351 --> 00:17:38.450
I know him. You know him.

206
00:17:38.895 --> 00:17:41.606
Has he done anything to make you think
that he would keep his word?

207
00:17:41.690 --> 00:17:42.857
- No.
- No.

208
00:17:42.941 --> 00:17:45.207
They're going to get through
that door eventually.

209
00:17:45.569 --> 00:17:46.750
Yes. they will.

210
00:17:47.863 --> 00:17:49.461
So let's be ready for them.

211
00:18:29.863 --> 00:18:31.044
Is that a…?

212
00:18:47.547 --> 00:18:49.674
Son… …what is this?

213
00:18:49.758 --> 00:18:51.106
Ah. oil?

214
00:18:51.593 --> 00:18:55.763
Uh. no. I think it's fuel.
It's like oil. but it burns faster.

215
00:18:55.847 --> 00:18:57.724
And... And this one is... Argh!

216
00:18:57.808 --> 00:18:59.601
Yeah. uh. it's a lamp.

217
00:18:59.685 --> 00:19:01.102
How do I explain this to you?

218
00:19:01.186 --> 00:19:04.355
Um. it... it brightens the dark
so we can see.

219
00:19:04.439 --> 00:19:05.787
God Flame in your hand.

220
00:19:06.149 --> 00:19:08.401
Uh. not quite.
but it does get really hot like fire.

221
00:19:08.485 --> 00:19:09.666
So be careful.

222
00:19:18.287 --> 00:19:22.762
Barrel. grip. magazine…

223
00:19:26.336 --> 00:19:27.517
…trigger.

224
00:19:29.381 --> 00:19:33.231
Only put your finger on the trigger
when you're ready to fire.

225
00:19:35.304 --> 00:19:40.113
And only point at
what you're willing to destroy.

226
00:20:16.011 --> 00:20:17.192
Ranger.

227
00:20:19.222 --> 00:20:20.403
I think we're good.

228
00:20:22.559 --> 00:20:24.241
It's a good day for some killing.

229
00:20:26.063 --> 00:20:28.328
All your talk about fighting
for no nation.

230
00:20:28.774 --> 00:20:30.024
And yet here you are.

231
00:20:30.108 --> 00:20:32.318
I'm not here for Pennsa. I'm here for you.

232
00:20:32.402 --> 00:20:35.836
And you're not here for Pennsa either.
you're here for your family.

233
00:20:37.658 --> 00:20:39.297
That's actually funny.

234
00:20:40.911 --> 00:20:43.969
The fate of an entire kingdom
rests upon the shoulders

235
00:20:44.414 --> 00:20:46.390
of two people
who couldn't care less about it.

236
00:20:49.211 --> 00:20:50.600
What is it?

237
00:20:52.631 --> 00:20:54.020
Huh?

238
00:20:54.841 --> 00:20:57.190
I can hear your thoughts from over there.

239
00:20:57.719 --> 00:21:00.277
It's what Tormada said
about my children.

240
00:21:00.931 --> 00:21:02.112
Oh.

241
00:21:03.976 --> 00:21:07.993
You have spent your life protecting them.

242
00:21:08.355 --> 00:21:11.037
Only to walk them into danger
again and again.

243
00:21:12.651 --> 00:21:17.252
I've met your children.
They're no longer children.

244
00:21:19.700 --> 00:21:21.465
They walk their own path now.

245
00:21:22.286 --> 00:21:24.704
There comes a time when the choice
is no longer yours.

246
00:21:24.788 --> 00:21:26.539
And that doesn't sit well with you.

247
00:21:26.623 --> 00:21:29.083
No. it does not.

248
00:21:29.167 --> 00:21:34.603
No. it does not. because you are a man who
enjoys telling other people what to do!

249
00:21:38.844 --> 00:21:40.192
Baba Voss…

250
00:21:42.055 --> 00:21:44.196
We may very well die here.

251
00:21:46.310 --> 00:21:50.410
Now. before we do.
there is something I must know.

252
00:21:54.067 --> 00:21:56.666
How is it that I'm never able
to sneak up on you?

253
00:21:59.948 --> 00:22:03.284
It's those giant balls
slamming up against your thighs.

254
00:22:03.368 --> 00:22:05.662
Mmm.

255
00:22:05.746 --> 00:22:09.582
Your left knee creaks every second step.

256
00:22:09.666 --> 00:22:10.667
What?

257
00:22:10.751 --> 00:22:12.599
It's how I can always hear you coming.

258
00:22:14.880 --> 00:22:16.728
Is that true?

259
00:22:17.257 --> 00:22:18.438
Very true.

260
00:22:38.904 --> 00:22:40.784
Make a hole.

261
00:23:03.303 --> 00:23:04.651
Shall we?

262
00:23:30.580 --> 00:23:31.720
Dad?

263
00:23:40.340 --> 00:23:42.439
There's too many walls in there.

264
00:23:43.010 --> 00:23:44.719
I just needed some fresh air.

265
00:23:46.555 --> 00:23:49.529
Yeah. I guess Jerlamarel liked
to close himself off from the world.

266
00:23:53.145 --> 00:23:54.868
It's what the ancestors did.

267
00:23:57.274 --> 00:23:59.623
They thought
they were protecting themselves.

268
00:24:00.902 --> 00:24:03.293
But they
were just locking themselves away.

269
00:24:04.615 --> 00:24:05.796
They were afraid.

270
00:24:08.744 --> 00:24:10.050
They were right to be.

271
00:24:11.330 --> 00:24:15.555
Baba Voss. you're out of time.
Hand over the children.

272
00:24:19.004 --> 00:24:20.894
Seems you misjudged them. Harlan.

273
00:24:21.381 --> 00:24:22.549
Let's go.

274
00:24:28.805 --> 00:24:30.612
You did all you could to save them.

275
00:24:32.267 --> 00:24:34.366
I imagine it won't take very long now.

276
00:24:35.687 --> 00:24:38.898
No. It's gonna take longer than you think.

277
00:24:59.002 --> 00:25:00.392
No resistance.

278
00:26:20.500 --> 00:26:21.681
Haniwa?

279
00:26:23.337 --> 00:26:25.018
- Go. go. go. go.
- Okay.

280
00:28:03.228 --> 00:28:05.939
- How many did you get?
- You go first. How many did you get?

281
00:28:06.023 --> 00:28:07.398
- Same time.
- Okay.

282
00:28:07.482 --> 00:28:09.025
- Six.
- Seven. I win.

283
00:28:49.816 --> 00:28:50.997
Oh. no.

284
00:28:56.073 --> 00:28:57.254
Sheva.

285
00:29:14.216 --> 00:29:16.314
The ringing in your ears will stop soon.

286
00:29:17.386 --> 00:29:18.469
Let's go.

287
00:29:23.225 --> 00:29:24.406
Haniwa.

288
00:29:43.161 --> 00:29:44.287
The bombs?

289
00:29:44.371 --> 00:29:45.969
- Ready to move.
- Follow me.

290
00:29:46.415 --> 00:29:47.415
Set!

291
00:31:10.499 --> 00:31:11.680
What's happening?

292
00:31:12.292 --> 00:31:14.335
You saved my life.
Now I'm gonna save yours.

293
00:31:14.419 --> 00:31:16.101
Stay still. Stay quiet.

294
00:31:18.465 --> 00:31:19.465
You say... What is this?

295
00:31:19.549 --> 00:31:21.481
Don't move. They're with me.

296
00:31:26.890 --> 00:31:29.156
- What have you done?
- I had to do this.

297
00:31:29.977 --> 00:31:31.158
Guntar.

298
00:31:31.561 --> 00:31:32.645
Harlan.

299
00:31:32.729 --> 00:31:33.910
You're late.

300
00:31:34.231 --> 00:31:35.871
You're welcome.

301
00:31:36.275 --> 00:31:38.039
Clear it up. We're moving out.

302
00:31:42.823 --> 00:31:45.617
- If you kill me. they will kill you.
- You betrayed me.

303
00:31:45.701 --> 00:31:47.076
Yeah. you betrayed me first.

304
00:31:47.160 --> 00:31:48.800
I offered you a new life.

305
00:31:49.913 --> 00:31:52.471
Turns out I was kind of attached
to my last one.

306
00:31:53.375 --> 00:31:56.169
We are going to destroy Pennsa
and everyone in it.

307
00:31:58.880 --> 00:32:01.062
Please. Trovere. Please.

308
00:32:01.800 --> 00:32:03.315
Don't make me do this.

309
00:32:04.344 --> 00:32:06.512
Trovere. please.

310
00:32:06.596 --> 00:32:08.556
Oh. shit. I'm so sorry.

311
00:32:08.640 --> 00:32:11.267
I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry.
I shouldn't have...

312
00:32:20.611 --> 00:32:21.694
I'm so sorry.

313
00:32:21.778 --> 00:32:25.114
You loved me. didn't you?

314
00:32:25.198 --> 00:32:26.379
At least a little?

315
00:32:29.661 --> 00:32:30.842
You know I did.

316
00:32:31.788 --> 00:32:33.289
You know I did. It's okay.

317
00:32:33.373 --> 00:32:35.347
You know I did.

318
00:32:55.937 --> 00:32:57.118
Dad?

319
00:32:58.190 --> 00:33:00.650
Dad? Dad?

320
00:33:00.734 --> 00:33:04.070
Kofun. Kofun.

321
00:33:04.154 --> 00:33:06.211
- You're okay? Yeah?
- I'm good. Boy. You?

322
00:33:06.531 --> 00:33:07.532
There were more.

323
00:33:07.616 --> 00:33:09.214
There's not.

324
00:33:14.206 --> 00:33:15.387
It's over.

325
00:33:15.707 --> 00:33:18.348
Baba. I've checked all the dead.

326
00:33:18.961 --> 00:33:20.475
Tormada's not here.

327
00:33:35.602 --> 00:33:36.783
Fuck!

328
00:33:39.773 --> 00:33:42.442
Harlan. Harlan!

329
00:33:42.526 --> 00:33:45.069
Baba. Time's of the essence.

330
00:33:45.153 --> 00:33:46.404
We gotta get the...

331
00:33:46.488 --> 00:33:47.530
Papa. Let him go.

332
00:33:47.614 --> 00:33:49.115
- You let this happen!
- Dad!

333
00:33:49.199 --> 00:33:50.200
I bought you time!

334
00:33:50.284 --> 00:33:52.118
His men killed
the rest of the Trivantians.

335
00:33:52.202 --> 00:33:54.204
- I don't trust you!
- I don't care!

336
00:33:54.288 --> 00:33:56.219
- Where is Tormada?
- He's gone.

337
00:33:58.667 --> 00:33:59.667
Fuck.

338
00:33:59.751 --> 00:34:01.085
And he took the bombs.

339
00:34:01.169 --> 00:34:04.227
- Where did he go?
- Fuck! It doesn't matter where he went.

340
00:34:04.881 --> 00:34:08.064
Fucking asshole. We know where he'll go.

341
00:34:08.427 --> 00:34:09.608
Pennsa.

342
00:34:10.426 --> 00:34:13.264
They can't be moving very quickly
if they've got those bombs with them.

343
00:34:13.348 --> 00:34:15.447
- Let's go.
- No. Kofun.

344
00:34:16.018 --> 00:34:17.310
No. We are going after him.

345
00:34:17.394 --> 00:34:19.020
There are numerous routes out of here.

346
00:34:19.104 --> 00:34:22.065
Even if we do manage to track them.
they're gonna be well protected.

347
00:34:22.149 --> 00:34:23.191
We're faster than them.

348
00:34:23.275 --> 00:34:27.445
Which is why we need to get to Pennsa.
Raise the alarm. Meet them with an army.

349
00:34:27.529 --> 00:34:30.281
- Harlan is right.
- What?

350
00:34:30.365 --> 00:34:32.700
If we take them on again.
we will be defeated.

351
00:34:32.784 --> 00:34:33.785
Look. Dad...

352
00:34:33.869 --> 00:34:35.912
Kofun. you are feeling energy
from the fight.

353
00:34:35.996 --> 00:34:38.553
But that will soon fade.
and your body will feel weak.

354
00:34:39.541 --> 00:34:42.752
We need to rest up for a bit.
and we will move swiftly to Pennsa. okay?

355
00:34:42.836 --> 00:34:43.962
I am not staying here.

356
00:34:44.046 --> 00:34:46.047
You need a fresh bandage.

357
00:34:46.131 --> 00:34:49.439
Okay? I can smell it. Trust me.

358
00:35:03.106 --> 00:35:06.943
Make sure they find her in her house.
Nobody needs to know she's a part of this.

359
00:35:07.027 --> 00:35:08.208
Understood.

360
00:35:18.162 --> 00:35:20.512
You're not going with them?

361
00:35:21.624 --> 00:35:24.641
Nah. I figured you'd need the company.

362
00:35:26.964 --> 00:35:29.311
You know.
this likely won't end well for us.

363
00:35:29.800 --> 00:35:32.398
Tell me something I don't know.

364
00:36:48.629 --> 00:36:50.101
- Kofun!
- Stop!

365
00:36:57.554 --> 00:36:59.861
- We have to stop him.
- No.

366
00:37:00.724 --> 00:37:04.269
Kofun… this is our legacy.

367
00:37:04.353 --> 00:37:07.355
It's Jerlamarel's legacy. It's not ours.

368
00:37:07.439 --> 00:37:10.692
This is more than him. It's more than us.

369
00:37:10.776 --> 00:37:13.542
This place has destroyed the lives
of everyone we've loved!

370
00:37:14.446 --> 00:37:16.906
Okay? And these bombs might just be
the end of everything.

371
00:37:16.990 --> 00:37:19.214
You're not burning bombs! Are you?

372
00:37:19.910 --> 00:37:22.161
There are centuries of knowledge
in there. you...

373
00:37:22.245 --> 00:37:24.539
- I can't let him burn it. I won't let him.
- No. no.

374
00:37:28.543 --> 00:37:29.919
Stop!

375
00:37:31.755 --> 00:37:32.978
You can't stop him.

376
00:37:48.563 --> 00:37:49.744
Are you serious?

377
00:37:50.315 --> 00:37:53.818
This place is all that we have left.
It will keep us safe.

378
00:37:53.902 --> 00:37:55.361
Says the one holding a gun.

379
00:37:55.445 --> 00:37:57.544
I can't let you take this from me.

380
00:37:59.324 --> 00:38:00.755
Haniwa. it's me.

381
00:38:02.494 --> 00:38:03.675
Drop the gun.

382
00:38:06.581 --> 00:38:07.762
Please? Drop it.

383
00:38:10.794 --> 00:38:11.794
Are you serious?

384
00:38:11.878 --> 00:38:14.130
You're actually gonna try and shoot me?
Your own brother!

385
00:38:14.214 --> 00:38:16.216
What the hell? You're gonna shoot me?

386
00:38:18.593 --> 00:38:19.677
Come here!

387
00:38:19.761 --> 00:38:21.401
Get over...

388
00:38:24.349 --> 00:38:28.742
- You can't do this! Stop! Stop it!
- No! No!

389
00:38:31.356 --> 00:38:35.568
Stop! Now! It's over!
Stop. it's done. It's over!

390
00:38:35.652 --> 00:38:38.821
Haniwa! Just stop it! Both of you!
We have to get out of here!

391
00:38:38.905 --> 00:38:41.254
- What did you do?
- Haniwa.

392
00:38:42.242 --> 00:38:45.495
Haniwa. I know. I'm sorry.

393
00:38:45.579 --> 00:38:49.012
We will die if we do not leave now.
I'm sorry.

394
00:40:04.032 --> 00:40:05.464
I miss our home.

395
00:40:06.618 --> 00:40:09.342
Take these children to safety
and then go there.

396
00:40:10.789 --> 00:40:12.749
I will make my way back to you.

397
00:40:12.833 --> 00:40:15.793
Don't become a Payan.

398
00:40:15.877 --> 00:40:19.339
I belong to no nation.

399
00:40:19.423 --> 00:40:21.354
You belong to me.

400
00:40:38.442 --> 00:40:39.748
Be strong. Haniwa.

401
00:40:44.406 --> 00:40:45.670
This place…

402
00:40:47.784 --> 00:40:50.217
With all of its knowledge...

403
00:40:52.831 --> 00:40:54.513
It was our way forward.

404
00:40:55.250 --> 00:40:59.059
If I know you. you'll find another way.

405
00:41:04.803 --> 00:41:06.109
But you'll come back?

406
00:41:07.387 --> 00:41:08.686
Missing me already?

407
00:41:08.930 --> 00:41:10.803
No.

408
00:41:13.185 --> 00:41:14.533
A little bit.

409
00:41:15.228 --> 00:41:17.911
I'll come back.

410
00:41:19.107 --> 00:41:22.624
Just do your best
to stay alive until I do. Okay?

411
00:41:23.362 --> 00:41:24.626
I will.

412
00:41:25.989 --> 00:41:27.170
Okay.

413
00:41:28.325 --> 00:41:30.382
Charlotte.

414
00:41:43.840 --> 00:41:46.189
Okay. Get out of here.

415
00:41:47.094 --> 00:41:49.442
Okay! Let's get going.

416
00:41:50.138 --> 00:41:55.115
Hayah. Hoveh. always behind me.
Sheva! Always behind them.

417
00:41:57.604 --> 00:41:58.785
Haniwa.

418
00:42:00.023 --> 00:42:01.913
Thank you for saving my family.

419
00:42:06.446 --> 00:42:08.412
Guess they were my family too.

420
00:42:09.490 --> 00:42:11.178
That means we're sisters.

421
00:42:17.165 --> 00:42:20.474
I'm sorry about your home.

422
00:42:25.173 --> 00:42:26.532
It's okay.

423
00:42:29.303 --> 00:42:30.766
There are others.

424
00:42:31.305 --> 00:43:31.397
